
[1]culture

   CULTURE, n. [L. See Cultivate.]

   1. The act of tilling and preparing the earth for crops; cultivation;
   the application of labor or other means of improvement.

   We ought to blame the culture, not the soil.

   2. The application of labor or other means to improve good qualities
   in, or growth; as the culture of the mind; the culture of virtue.

   3. The application of labor or other means in producing; as the culture
   of corn, or grass.

   4. Any labor or means employed for improvement, correction or growth.

                         CULTURE, v.t. To cultivate.
